{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 17:17:54,150", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T17:17:54.150586\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Develop gem transformation and match logic: convert locked tetromino blocks into colored gems, detect Tetris line clears and Bejeweled match-3 patterns, trigger chain reactions, and update score.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\nfrom enum import Enum, auto\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple\\n\\n# Grid dimensions\\nGRID_WIDTH = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\nCELL_SIZE = 30\\n\\n# Cell states\\nclass CellState(Enum):\\n    EMPTY = auto()      # No block or gem\\n    FALLING = auto()    # Part of current tetromino\\n    GEM = auto()        # Locked-in gem\\n\\n# Gem color types (indexed 0–6)\\nclass GemColor(Enum):\\n    RED = 0\\n    GREEN = 1\\n    BLUE = 2\\n    YELLOW = 3\\n    CYAN = 4\\n    MAGENTA = 5\\n    ORANGE = 6\\n\\n# RGB mapp...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"Here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The line-clear test is inverted: it clears rows with NO gems instead of rows FULL of gems. You need  \\n   `if all(cell.is_gem() for cell in row)`  \\n   not `if all(not cell.is_gem() for cell in row)`.\\n2. After matches are cleared, the remaining gems never “fall down,” so you never get true chain reactions. You must implement an `apply_gravity()` that collapses gems in each column.\\n3. In `clear_lines_and_matches()`, you should clear lines first, then matches, then call `apply_gravity()`, update the score, and recurse only if anything was cleared.\\n4. The scoring and recursion logic needs to happen after gravity so that new matches from falling gems can be detected.\\n\\nHere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport random\\nfrom enum import Enum, auto\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple\\n\\n# Grid dimensions\\nGRID_WIDTH = 10\\nGRID_HEIGHT = 20\\n\\nclass CellState(Enum):\\n    EMPTY = auto()\\n    FALLING = auto()\\n    GEM = auto()\\n\\nclass GemColor(Enum):\\n    RED = 0\\n    GREEN = 1\\n    BLUE = 2\\n    YELLOW = 3\\n    CYAN = 4\\n    MAGENTA = 5\\n    ORANGE = 6\\n\\nclass Cell:\\n    def __init__(self, state: CellState = CellState.EMPTY, color: GemColor = None):\\n        self.state = state\\n        self.color = color\\n\\n    def reset(self):\\n        self.state = CellState.EMPTY\\n        self.color = None\\n\\n    def is_empty(self) -> bool:\\n        return self.state == CellState.EMPTY\\n\\n    def is_falling(self) -> bool:\\n        return self.state == CellState.FALLING\\n\\n    def is_gem(self) -> bool:\\n        return self.state == CellState.GEM\\n\\ndef create_grid() -> List[List[Cell]]:\\n    return [[Cell() for _ in range(GRID_WIDTH)] for _ in range(GRID_HEIGHT)]\\n\\n# (Tetromino definitions omitted for brevity; assume lock_into_grid works)\\n\\nclass GameState:\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.grid = create_grid()\\n        self.score = 0\\n        # ... current_tetromino, next_tetromino setup omitted ...\\n\\n    def clear_falling(self):\\n        for row in self.grid:\\n            for cell in row:\\n                if cell.is_falling():\\n                    cell.reset()\\n\\n    def apply_gravity(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Collapse all GEMs downward in each column.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n            stack = []\\n            for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT):\\n                if self.grid[y][x].is_gem():\\n                    stack.append(self.grid[y][x].color)\\n            # refill column from bottom up\\n            for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT - 1, -1, -1):\\n                if stack:\\n                    self.grid[y][x].state = CellState.GEM\\n                    self.grid[y][x].color = stack.pop()\\n                else:\\n                    self.grid[y][x].reset()\\n\\n    def clear_lines_and_matches(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Clears full lines and 3+ gem matches, applies gravity, updates score,\\n        and recurses for chain reactions.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # 1) Clear full GEM lines\\n        lines_cleared = 0\\n        for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT):\\n            if all(self.grid[y][x].is_gem() for x in range(GRID_WIDTH)):\\n                # clear that row\\n                for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n                    self.grid[y][x].reset()\\n                # shift rows above down\\n                for yy in range(y, 0, -1):\\n                    for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n                        self.grid[yy][x].state = self.grid[yy-1][x].state\\n                        self.grid[yy][x].color = self.grid[yy-1][x].color\\n                # clear top row\\n                for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n                    self.grid[0][x].reset()\\n                lines_cleared += 1\\n\\n        # 2) Clear 3+ matches\\n        matches = self.find_matches()\\n        for x, y in matches:\\n            self.grid[y][x].reset()\\n        matches_cleared = len(matches)\\n\\n        # 3) If anything was cleared, apply gravity, update score, recurse\\n        if lines_cleared > 0 or matches_cleared > 0:\\n            # score: 100 per line, 50 per gem cleared in matches\\n            self.score += lines_cleared * 100\\n            self.score += matches_cleared * 50\\n            # gems fall down\\n            self.apply_gravity()\\n            # check for new cascades\\n            self.clear_lines_and_matches()\\n\\n    def find_matches(self) -> List[Tuple[int,int]]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return list of coordinates of all gems part of any 3+ horizontal or vertical match.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = set()\\n        # horizontal\\n        for y in range(GRID_HEIGHT):\\n            x = 0\\n            while x < GRID_WIDTH - 2:\\n                if self.grid[y][x].is_gem():\\n                    color = self.grid[y][x].color\\n                    length = 1\\n                    while x + length < GRID_WIDTH and self.grid[y][x+length].is_gem() and self.grid[y][x+length].color == color:\\n                        length += 1\\n                    if length >= 3:\\n                        for i in range(length):\\n                            matches.add((x+i, y))\\n                    x += length\\n                else:\\n                    x += 1\\n        # vertical\\n        for x in range(GRID_WIDTH):\\n            y = 0\\n            while y < GRID_HEIGHT - 2:\\n                if self.grid[y][x].is_gem():\\n                    color = self.grid[y][x].color\\n                    length = 1\\n                    while y + length < GRID_HEIGHT and self.grid[y+length][x].is_gem() and self.grid[y+length][x].color == color:\\n                        length += 1\\n                    if length >= 3:\\n                        for i in range(length):\\n                            matches.add((x, y+i))\\n                    y += length\\n                else:\\n                    y += 1\\n        return list(matches)\\n\\n    # Call clear_falling() before lock and spawn in your tick/update loop,\\n    # then after locking the tetromino into GEMs, call clear_lines_and_matches().\\n\\n# Now the grid will correctly clear full lines, detect match-3, let remaining gems fall,\\n# award points, and support chain reactions.\\n```\"}"}
